  "prompt": "How hot does Austin, TX get?",
  "response": "Austin, TX experiences a range of temperatures throughout the year, with the summer months being particularly hot. During peak summer, especially in July and August, temperatures often soar into the high 90s and can sometimes exceed 100\u00b0F (37.8\u00b0C). Heatwaves can push temperatures even higher occasionally. Winters are milder, with averages ranging from the 40s to 60s\u00b0F (4 to 20\u00b0C). It's advisable to stay hydrated and take measures to stay cool during the extreme heat periods.",
